properties.message: "You know this dainty monster, too, it seems, hypocrite adventurer!"
"You again. Far more than Life, The subtle bonds of Death around us twine."
"Thou givest me the beauty of divine caresses. Without pity or mercy we will fight."
"Oh. I cannot like a love-leaf wantonly Consign this stunted monster to the glowing grate."
"Oh cursed be that transient night of vain desire When I conceived my expiation in my womb!"
"Ah, why did I not bear a serpent's nest entire, Instead of bringing forth this hideous Child of Doom!"
"As an unfathomed sphinx, enthroned by the Nile, My heart a swan's whiteness with granite combines."
"The panting swain that o'er his mistress sighs, Seems the Sick, that stroke their gravestones lovingly."
"I advance to attack, and I climb to assault, Like a swarm of maggots after a cadaver."
"The thunder and the rain have made such ravage My garden is nigh bare of rosy fruit."
"Rembrandt, gloomy hospital filled with murmuring, Ornamented only with a large crucifix."
"Far from famous sepulchers Toward a lonely cemetery My heart Goes beating funeral marches."
"You could count in your beds More kisses than fleurs-de-lis And subject to your power Many Valois!"
"My spirit resembles the tower which crumbles Under the tireless blows of the battering ram."
"Kisses and bite, Tortures the breast of an old witch. Steal as we pass by a clandestine pleasure."
"I should have loved to have lived Beside a maiden giantess, Like a luxurious cat at the feet of a queen."
"In days when Christian seeds bloomed o'er the land, the monk Exalted Death in rude and simple way."
"Come, superb cat. My hand tingles with the pleasure Of feeling your electric body."
"Angel of gaiety, have you known anguish, Shame and remorse, tears, boredom, and dismay?"
"Tight, swarming, like a million worms, A population of Demons carries on in our brains."
"The Demon makes secret holes in this abyss, Whence would escape a thousand years of sweat and strain."
"The Living Torches, they save, Towards the Path of Joy they guide my ways."
"When by an edict of the powers supreme A poet's born into this world's drab space."
"His mother starts, in horror, to blaspheme Clenching her fists at God, who grants her grace."
"Poets, before my grandiose poses, Will consume their lives in austere study."
"I was 6 when verses stopped blooming in the fields like roses."
"In her grief, The Mother, chaste and thin, was Near her treacherous spouse who was once her lover. "
"Obeying a curious whim, I had banned studies from that spectacle."
"Sweltering Africa and languorous Asia, A whole far-away world, absent, almost defunct."
"Disease and Death make ashes Of all the fire that flamed for us."
"He smokes his hookah, while he dreams Of gibbets, weeping tears he cannot smother. "
"This world will soon end, at the foot of the delicious terrible catafalque."
"I was happy, healthy, and sated; As for me, my arms are weary Because I have embraced the clouds."
